text:
Serena Williams celebrated her upcoming wedding with her loved ones on Friday night, gathering with 12 guests for a glamorous pre-wedding girls' weekend.

The four-time Olympic gold medalist, 36, is seen in exclusive images and video with her sister Venus, 37, best friend Ciara, 32, and TV presenter Lala Anthony, 38, during the bash in New York City. Serena, who is engaged to Reddit co-founder Alexis Ohanian, 34, arrived with her 12 guests on a party bus to her chosen venue for the first part of the evening.

There, the new mother enjoyed an elegant dinner served by male waiters in a lavish room, with her mother Oracene Price, 65, joining the guests around a long table.

Scroll down for video

Party on: Serena Williams celebrated her upcoming wedding with her loved ones (including Ciara, right) on Friday night, gathering with 12 guests for a glamorous pre-wedding party

Gathering: The four-time Olympic gold medalist, 36, was spotted with her sister Venus, 37, best friend Ciara, 32, and TV presenter Lala Anthony, 38, during the bash

Night out: Venus was seen stepping out for her sister's pre-wedding girls' weekend in a mini dress, black low boots, and a small crossover bag

BFFs: Lala was seen stepping out alongside Venus during the night of celebration

Group: Serena wore a bright blue mini dress with a funny face on it, paired with black knee-high group. Ciara went with a black dress and black lace-up boots with a leather jacket

Serena was raised as a Jehovah's witness, and while she told Vogue she has 'never really practiced' the religion, she said it remained 'important' to her. Jehovah's witnesses don't eschew drinking alcohol and partying, but believe both should be done in moderation.

The new mother gave birth in September to her first child, a daughter named Alexis Olympia Ohanian, Jr. She and her partner announced their engagement back in December 2016 but have so far kept the exact wedding date under wraps.

However, last month DailyMailTV revealed that Serena and her fiance met with their wedding planner in New Orleans, flying from their home in Florida to spend the day in the Big Easy preparing for the ceremony.

The couple spent more than an hour inside Meril, an upmarket restaurant, in the city's warehouse district, owned by celebrity chef Emeril Lagasse, and are thought to have been discussing the menu options and other arrangements for their nuptials - thought to be taking place within the next few weeks.

Serena, who won the 2017 Australian Open while eight weeks pregnant, previously pledged to the courts soon after her daughter's birth, and was eyeing the next Australian Open, which will take place in January 2018, as a possible stage for her comeback.

Joy: Serena seemed to be enjoying herself as she celebrated her big night in New York City with some of her closest friends

Let's eat! The new mother enjoyed an elegant dinner served by male waiters in an elegant room, with her mother Oracene Price, 65, joining the guests around a long table

Sisters: During the evening, Serena shared a fun video of her sister dancing, joking that Venus was wearing a lovely 'T-shirt' in lieu of a dress

Convenient: A party bus took Venus, Serena and the rest of the guests to several locations over the course of the evening

Decor: The dining room was decorated with a balloon shaped like an engagement ring, setting the tone of the evening

Sweet! A four-tier cake covered in pink frosting and sparkly decorations was also ready for the dessert course

Ride: The party bus rented by Serena and her friends appears to have come from Ultimate Party Bus, a New-Jersey-based limo company; its buses come with 'safety/dance poles'

Dress code? Lala also went for an all-black outfit, opting for ripped jeans and high boots

On Friday, the dining room that hosted Serena and her guests was decorated with a balloon shaped like an engagement ring, setting the tone of the evening.

A four-tier cake covered in pink frosting and sparkly decorations was also ready for the dessert course.

The party bus rented by Serena and her friends appears to have come from Ultimate Party Bus, a New-Jersey-based limo company, whose buses are equipped with mutli-function 'safety/dance poles'.

They also include multicolored DJ lighting, a stereo and CD player, and, of course, a bathroom.

After chatting around the dinner table, Serena and her guests got the party started with a DJ.

They left the party room at midnight, and headed to hit the club scene. The group partied at the PH-D Rooftop at the Dream Downtown, north of the Meatpacking district, until 3am, before all getting back on the bus.

To end the evening, they headed to a five-star Baccarat Hotel and Residences.

The following night, the gang then headed to dinner at Legasea at Moxy Times Square.

Helpful: Male waiters made sure Serena and her loved ones had everything they needed during the dinner at the start of the evening

It begins: After chatting around the dinner table, Serena and her guests got the party started with a DJ

Schedule: Serena's bash began with an elegant dinner around a long table, decorated with bright pink flowers in its center

Missing: While several of Serena's friends attended the event, some of her famous pals, such as Kim Kardashian and Beyonce, were a no-show

Squad: Serena was accompanied by her friends as the group made its way around the city aboard a rented party bus

Friends: Lala and Ciara were among the 12 guests who came to celebrate Serena's engagement

Good fun: Serena seemed in high spirits as she and her entourage gathered at the table

Are you lost? Ciara at one point ended up in a rather barren-looking location, along with one of the guests who kept a water bottle at hand

Serena Hosted at the opulent Baccarat Hotel & Residences, the first hotel from France's eponymous crystal brand, the Girl’s Weekend included five-star spa treatments, trapeze'ing, tea brunches, dinner and dancing out on the town.

Williams was joined by her sister, Venus Williams and close friends Lala Anthony, and music artist Ciara, among others.

The weekend kicked off in Serena's suite followed by a luxe brunch in the Petite Salon with a customized menu prepared by the chef at the Baccarat Hotel. The evening continued with a dinner in the private dining room of Legasea, New York's newest Seafood Brassiere. The ladies also enjoyed specialty cocktails and late-night dancing at Magic Hour Rooftop Bar & Lounge and PHD Rooftop Lounge.

The weekend concluded with pampering by the luxurious Spa de La Mer at the Baccarat Hotel and lounging poolside in the cabanas inspired by the Côte d'Azur.

Serena Williams & Venus Williams Toast the Kickoff of Their Girls Weekend at Baccarat Hotel & Residences

Family: Serena is engaged to Reddit co-founder Alexis Ohanian, pictured holding their baby daughter Alexis Olympia Ohanian Jr. after a bath

Mom and dad: The new mother became engaged to Alexis (pictured with her) in December 2016; they have so far kept their wedding date under wraps

Mid-yawn: Serena Williams shared a sweet snap of herself bonding with her two-month-old daughter Alexis Olympia on Monday morning

During the evening, Serena shared a fun video of her sister dancing, joking that Venus was wearing a lovely 'T-shirt' in lieu of a dress.

While Serena was surrounded by her loved ones on the fun night, several of her famous friends were missing from the festivities, including Kim Kardashian and Beyonce.

But while Serena no doubt enjoyed a night off from her duties as a mother - she happily waxed lyrical about her baby daughter during an appearance on CNBC's Squawk Box on Monday morning.

When asked how 'great it is being a mom', the tennis pro laughed and said: 'It's great being a mom,' before going on to discuss whether she plans for the baby girl to follow in her footsteps on the courts.

'Every tennis player is like, "We don't want our kids to be tennis players!" and I fall exactly in that same [category],' she said.

'My fiance insists that she's going to be in tech and business and stuff like that.'
